From Bill Vojak Subject Letter To David Skaggs Here is a letter I sent to David Skaggs Dem CO Before anybody says something yes the letter is a bit sharp in I have been writting reasonable and polite letters to him for years and all I get in return in the HCI party Since he already is NRA F rated I don't think that upsetting him will harm the Sorry if you disagree but recent events in Texas REALLY have me April Representative Skaggs Recently I wrote to you regarding my outrage over the tactics used by the Bureau of Alcohol Tobacco and Firearms BATF in In your response you stated that Events in Texas underscore the need for stricter gun control legislation to keep guns out of the hand of groups such as the Branch My question to you is what grounds would you use to deny them access to firearms Best I can tell this statement underscores your apparent total ignorance of the subject and highlights your personal bias against I say this because there are only two possible paths of gun control which you could have been Either You were talking about their access to semi automatics In this case I should point out that semi automatic firearms are legal in most areas of this Country including Texas and In addition the members of the cult have never been convicted of any crimes which would deny them the ability to purchase these So under what grounds would you deny them these guns Their religion The fact they they live in a large group alone by themselves Because you consider them to be a cult Maybe I consider your Church to be a cult This line of reasoning by you borders on the concept of thought You and Pat Robertson should really get You were referring to the ALLEGED FULLY automatic weapons possessed by the Under current US law FULLY automatic weapons have been covered by some of the strictest gun control laws in this So if David Koresh illegally possessed them he would have had to circumvent some of the strictest laws we How will more laws help By the way it has been reported that David Koresh possessed a Federal Firearms License which would have permitted him to possess FULLY automatic If true the people who perished Monday in the fire died so that the Federal government could collect a couple hundred dollars in taxes on guns David Koresh didn't I have heard claims that they were stockpiling Yet considering the number of people in the complex even weapons would not have been out of line with gun ownership statistics for all of What's next A siege of Dallas Ft Worth for alleged stockpiling Face it David Skaggs You have voted for virtually EVERY gun control law that has passed through Congress yet you claim that you are only for reasonable Bull Handgun Control is struggling to maintain PAID members while the NRA has just exceeded They are still growing at a rate of new members per Driving around YOUR district I see NRA stickers every In eight plus years of living here I have only seen ONE HCI bumper When you vote for your reasonable gun control laws are you really representing your district or are you representing Sarah Bradys' Thank You William Vojak April Representative Skaggs Recently I wrote to you regarding my outrage over the tactics used by the Bureau of Alcohol Tobacco and Firearms BATF in In your response you stated that Events in Texas underscore the need for stricter gun control legislation to keep guns out of the hand of groups such as the Branch My question to you is what grounds would you use to deny them access to firearms Best I can tell this statement underscores your apparent total ignorance of the subject and highlights your personal bias against I say this because there are only two possible paths of gun control which you could have been Either You were talking about their access to semi automatics In this case I should point out that semi automatic firearms are legal in most areas of this Country including Texas and In addition the members of the cult have never been convicted of any crimes which would deny them the ability to purchase these So under what grounds would you deny them these guns Their religion The fact they they live in a large group alone by themselves Because you consider them to be a cult Maybe I consider your Church to be a cult This line of reasoning by you borders on the concept of thought You and Pat Robertson should really get You were referring to the ALLEGED FULLY automatic weapons possessed by the Under current US law FULLY automatic weapons have been covered by some of the strictest gun control laws in this So if David Koresh illegally possessed them he would have had to circumvent some of the strictest laws we How will more laws help By the way it has been reported that David Koresh possessed a Federal Firearms License which would have permitted him to possess FULLY automatic If true the people who perished Monday in the fire died so that the Federal government could collect a couple hundred dollars in taxes on guns David Koresh didn't I have heard claims that they were stockpiling Yet considering the number of people in the complex even weapons would not have been out of line with gun ownership statistics for all of What's next A siege of Dallas Ft Worth for alleged stockpiling Face it David Skaggs You have voted for virtually EVERY gun control law that has passed through Congress yet you claim that you are only for reasonable Bull Handgun Control is struggling to maintain PAID members while the NRA has just exceeded They are still growing at a rate of new members per Driving around YOUR district I see NRA stickers every In eight plus years of living here I have only seen ONE HCI bumper When you vote for your reasonable gun control laws are you really representing your district or are you representing Sarah Bradys' Thank You William Vojak Bill Vojak NRA ILA Colorado Firearms Coalition The CBS Nightly Propaganda With Dan RATHER NOT The CBS Nightly Propaganda With Dan RATHER BIASED